#! # _TikBook_ - the VSCode Notebook for MikroTik RouterOS
#! 
#! 
#! You can run RouterOS scripts, and use markdown for notes. I add some text......
#! 
#! 
#! 

:put "And, when saved I am also a valid RouterOS script (`.rsc`) too and code too"




#! 
#! Since VSCode Notebook can "run" cells, you can get the router's IP address into the notebook
#! 
#! 
#! 
#! 
/ip/address/print




#! 
#! > Allowing RouterOS script to **also* be a valid VSCode notebook is dirt simple with the [RouterOS LSP]().
#! > Since the LSP needs a valid connection into the REST API to a MikroTik device for
#! > `/console/inspect` that powers that LSP – but this can be used to run Notebook cells too.
#! > It's less than 100 lines in LSP since VSCode notebook support two types:
#! >  * `Markup` which is markdown, and "serialized" using the `#!` back from VS Code
#! >  * `Code`
#! > A line start with `#!` in still comment in RouterOS, but the exclamation <kbd>!<kbd> 
#! 
#! 
#! 
/console/inspect request=syntax path=ip,address,print



#! 
#! 
#! 
#! 


/container/print





/container stop 0
